        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 5:38PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 538 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Seeley Lake to 8 miles
southwest of Drummond. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Drummond, Ovando, Garrison, Seeley Lake, Maxville, Jens, Brock Creek,
New Chicago, Clearwater, Bearmouth, Garnet, Helmville, Goldcreek,
Hall, Woodworth, and Greenough.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between mile markers 140 and 173.
Highway 83 between mile markers 0 and 13.
Highway 200 E between mile markers 25 and 63.
</description>
        <instruction>These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
